   "source": [
    "# LLM-Based Global Travel Concierge: Safety, Compliance & Evaluation Notebook\n",
    "### Securing AI Agents with PII Scrubber Guardrails & Location-Specific Behavioral Constraints\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook provides a complete hands-on guide, demonstration dataset, safety logic, and evaluation harness for a production-grade **LLM-Based Global Travel Concierge**. \n",
    "\n",
    "Our system provides highly personalized, budget-conscious global itineraries. However, deploying such a concierge introduces critical challenges:\n",
    "1. **Information Privacy (PII Leaks)**: Users often write personal details (emails, phone numbers, secret API keys) into itinerary preference boxes.\n",
    "2. **Location-Specific Compliance**: System advice must remain accurate over time (e.g., deprecation of local ticketing platforms like India's unreserved 'UTS' app in favor of 'Railone').\n",
    "\n",
    "---"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 0. Get the Project\n",
    "\n",
    "To build, run, and explore the complete full-stack web application accompanying this evaluation suite:\n",
    "\n",
    "### Source Architecture & Stack:\n",
    "- **Frontend**: React 18, Vite, Tailwind CSS, Lucide Icons, and Motion for sleek fluid layout animations.\n",
    "- **Backend**: Express.js server in TypeScript, mounting Vite in dev mode and pre-compiling via `esbuild` for CJS production runtimes on Cloud Run.\n",
    "- **AI Core**: Google Gemini 2.5 Flash SDK (`@google/genai` TypeScript client).\n",
    "\n",
    "### Local Setup Instructions:\n",
    "```bash\n",
    "# 1. Clone the repository\n",
    "git clone <your-repository-url>\n",
    "cd travel-concierge-app\n",
    "\n",
    "# 2. Install all development & production dependencies\n",
    "npm install\n",
    "\n",
    "# 3. Configure local environment variables\n",
    "cp .env.example .env\n",
    "# Open .env and insert your GEMINI_API_KEY\n",
    "\n",
    "# 4. Launch the application in development mode\n",
    "npm run dev\n",
    "```\n",
    "Your application will run at **`http://localhost:3000`** with real-time API routes under `/api/*` proxies!"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. System Architecture\n",
    "\n",
    "Below is the comprehensive operational flow of the system. Notice how the safety guardrail acts as an intermediary firewall on both **ingress** (input to Gemini) and **egress** (output from Gemini to client).\n",
    "\n",
    "```\n",
    "    +------------------------------------------+\n",
    "    |           User Input Interface           |\n",
    "    |    (Travel Preferences / Custom Info)    |\n",
    "    +--------------------+---------------------+\n",
    "                         | \n",
    "                         v\n",
    "    +------------------------------------------+\n",
    "    |       Client/Server Ingress Shield       |\n",
    "    |    Redacts email, phone, cards, secrets  |\n",
    "    +--------------------+---------------------+\n",
    "                         | \n",
    "                         | [PII Sanitized Payload]\n",
    "                         v\n",
    "    +------------------------------------------+\n",
    "    |          Gemini 2.5 Flash API            |\n",
    "    |   Includes location-aware system rules   |\n",
    "    +--------------------+---------------------+\n",
    "                         | \n",
    "                         | [Raw JSON Response]\n",
    "                         v\n",
    "    +------------------------------------------+\n",
    "    |        Egress Sanitization Buffer        |\n",
    "    |   Detects & filters accidental echoes    |\n",
    "    +--------------------+---------------------+\n",
    "                         | \n",
    "                         v\n",
    "    +------------------------------------------+\n",
    "    |       Rendered Safety Travel Plans       |\n",
    "    |          (Presented to User)             |\n",
    "    +------------------------------------------+\n",
    "```"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. The Synthetic Dataset\n",
    "\n",
    "Let us create a synthetic evaluation dataset representing various edge cases: dirty prompts containing PII, country-specific locations (India vs Rest of World), and extreme travel budgets to thoroughly validate our system's behavior."
   ]
  },
  {
